-- Dowa Holdings to Increase Zinc Production 11% in Second Half Fiscal Year
-- B y   J a e   H u r   a n d   I c h i r o   S u z u k i
-- 2010-10-05T02:20:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/dowa-holdings-to-increase-zinc-production-11-in-second-half-fiscal-year.html
Dowa Holdings Co.  will increase its
monthly output of refined zinc by 11 percent in the second half
of this fiscal year compared with a year earlier.  The Tokyo-based company plans to produce 13,107 metric tons
a month in the six months to March 31, compared with 11,803 tons
a year earlier, the company said in a faxed statement today.  Dowa also projects monthly output of refined copper at
9,196 tons in the second half, down 1.2 percent from 9,311 tons
a year earlier. The following table gives monthly production in
tons for copper, zinc, lead and silver. Gold is in kilograms.  To contact the reporters on this story:
